Subject: [PATCH 2/2] theme: Fix jagged edges on notification buttons

On hover, notification buttons would get jagged edges instead of
smoothly rounded corners. This is a rendering glitch that can happen
when the background color changes.

To fix this, we apply a transparent inset box-shadow to the button.
This acts as a hint to the GPU to enforce proper anti-aliasing on
the corners, ensuring they remain smooth during transitions.
---
 data/theme/gnome-shell-sass/_common.scss | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/data/theme/gnome-shell-sass/_common.scss b/data/theme/gnome-shell-sass/_common.scss
index 846427e8e..9bf988a5d 100644
--- a/data/theme/gnome-shell-sass/_common.scss
+++ b/data/theme/gnome-shell-sass/_common.scss
@@ -198,6 +198,8 @@ stage {
   font-weight: bold;
   padding: $base_padding $base_padding * 2;
   border-radius: $base_border_radius;
+  border-width: 0;
+  box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 1px transparent;
 
   @include button(normal, $style: notification);
   &:focus { @include button(focus, $style: notification);}
